  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responding to Typhoon Goni (Rolly) in Bicol</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 1 November 2020, Super Typhoon Goni made landfall in the Bicol region (Philippines) as the world&apos;s most powerful storm of the year.  The Humanitarian Country Team published an initial report on 9 November, highlighting critical needs in areas including shelter and water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH). This project focuses on the provinces of Albay, Catanduanes and Camarines Sur, based on the extent of damage and number of affected populations, and identified gaps in the relief response and IOM rapid assessments. IOM is partnering with Catholic Relief Services (CRS) to provide flexible shelter solutions for 3,200 households, support 6,000 households with WASH and mental health and psychosocial support.</narrative>
  </description>
